{
  "document_id": "job-9",
  "title": "Job 9",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-heading-job-replies:-there-i",
      "type": "heading",
      "text": "Job Replies: There Is No Mediator"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "Then Job answered:"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "“Indeed, I know that this is so,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "If one wished to contend with him,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "He is wise in heart and mighty in strength;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "He removes mountains, and they do not know it"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "he shakes the earth out of its place,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "he commands the sun, and it does not rise;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "he alone stretched out the heavens"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "he made the Bear and Orion,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "he does great things beyond understanding"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "Look, he passes by me, and I do not see him;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "He snatches away; who can stop him?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "“God will not turn back his anger;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "How then can I answer him,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "Though I am innocent, I cannot answer him;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "If I summoned him and he answered me,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "For he crushes me with a tempest"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "he will not let me get my breath"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "If it is a contest of strength, he is the strong one!"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "Though I am innocent, my own mouth would condemn me;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "I am blameless; I do not know myself;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "It is all one; therefore I say,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "When disaster brings sudden death,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "The earth is given into the hand of the wicked;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "“My days are swifter than a runner;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "They go by like skiffs of reed,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "If I say, ‘I will forget my complaint;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "I become afraid of all my suffering,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "I shall be condemned;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "If I wash myself with soap"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-31",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 31,
      "text": "yet you will plunge me into filth,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-32",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 32,
      "text": "For he is not a mortal, as I am, that I might answer him,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-33",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 33,
      "text": "There is no mediator between us,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-34",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 34,
      "text": "If he would take his rod away from me"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-9-35",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 35,
      "text": "then I would speak without fear of him,"
    }
  ]
}